			<title>User List Module</title>
			<link>http://www.sigsiu.net/download/modules/user_list_module.html</link>
			<description>This module provides the logged in Sobi2 user with a list of his/her entry details. The module should preferably be shown under the usermenu. 
 
Installation 
Go to Menus --&gt; usermenu and click on &quot;new&quot;. Then, select a menu item type of User --&gt; Default User Layout. This page layout will have a default &quot;welcome message&quot; which you can use as it is, or you can edit and even remove. The welcome message can be edited in the WELCOME_DESC key of com_user.ini (site language folder). 
 
Then select banner position above (it will work in other positions, but banner position is preferred). Finally, make sure the module is set be displayed only under the menu link you just created. 
 
Settings 
Make your preferred settings in the panel to the right. If you want to change the date format, you may have a look at date function settings (http://php.net/date) on http://php.net/. 
 
Description of table 
The table displays entry information like entry ID, entry title (with link to details view), entry status (published, expired and unpublished/unapproved), number of hits, date of creation, number of days until expiration and the amount of payment associated with each entry (except expired entries). The module can be configured to also display the &quot;Delete&quot; and &quot;Edit&quot; buttons, as well as a &quot;Renew&quot; link (when the entry is about to expire, or has expired).</description>
			<pubDate>Sun, 13 Sep 2009 12:20:14 +0200</pubDate>
		</item>
